                                    <div class="homepage-section__title">
                                        <a href="projects/">Projects</a>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="homepage-section__content">
                                                            <div class="preview-project preview-project--homepage">




                        <a href="/projects/454815/you-can-t-trust-music/" class="preview-project__image js-open-overlayer" data="1.7777777777778">
                            <img class="js-lazyload lazyimage" data-src="https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1600" data-srcset="https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,100 100w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,200 200w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,300 300w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,400 400w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,500 500w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,640 640w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,750 750w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,828 828w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1024 1024w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1125 1125w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1242 1242w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1280 1280w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1400 1400w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1500 1500w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1600 1600w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1700 1700w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1800 1800w,https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,1920 1920w" data-sizes="auto" alt="" src="https://images.e-flux-systems.com/YCTM_PROJECT_PAGE_IMAGE_1920_x_1080_updated.png,ht">
                        </a>
                        <div class="preview-project__content">
                            <div class="preview-project__title">
                                <a href="/projects/454815/you-can-t-trust-music/" class="js-open-overlayer">
                                    You Can’t Trust Music
                                </a>
                            </div>

                            <div class="preview-project__text">
                                <p>Unlike literature or art, music appears to be nonrepresentational, at least at first.&nbsp;“But music also&nbsp;is&nbsp;a place of sorts,”&nbsp;says musicologist Holly Watkins,&nbsp;“replete with its own metaphorical locations, types of motion, departures, arrivals, and returns.”&nbsp;Songs articulate distance, texture, and intent. They respond to the acoustics of landscapes and social structures; they are amplified in some spaces and dampened in others.&nbsp;By listening to sounds—and the way they&nbsp;have been transcribed, adapted, and memorialized—we can trace otherwise invisible political interventions into landscapes and soundscapes and, in return, understand these interventions as documents, instructions, or scores.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            
